TAG Immobilien AG , a Hamburg-based
realtor, offered 4.50 euros a share for the remaining stake in
 Bau-Verein zu Hamburg AG  it doesnâ€™t own.  TAG, which owns 93.2 percent of Bau-Verein, gave
shareholders until March 9 to decide whether to accept the
offer, according to an e-mailed statement from TAG.  Bau-Verein sells, develops, leases and manages residential
and commercial real estate, primarily in Munich, Berlin and
Hamburg, and has a market capitalization of 101 million euros
($134 million), according to  data  compiled by Bloomberg.  To contact the reporter on this story:
